detailed_results.query: What are the GST requirements for my startup in New Zealand?
detailed_results.response:
Key GST (Goods and Services Tax) requirements for New Zealand startups:

1. Registration Requirements:
   • Mandatory registration when turnover exceeds or is expected to exceed NZD 60,000 in any 12-month period
   • Voluntary registration possible even if below the threshold
   • Current GST rate is 15%

2. Filing Frequency:
   • 6-monthly returns for businesses with turnover under $500,000
   • Due dates: February 5 and September 5

3. Important Notes:
   • Must register as soon as you expect to exceed the $60,000 threshold
   • Penalties may apply for late registration
   • Non-resident businesses providing taxable supplies in NZ must also register if they exceed the threshold

4. Compliance:
   • Need to keep track of all GST collected from customers
   • Must maintain records of GST paid on business expenses
   • Required to file returns and pay GST by due dates
